# Google Sheets (reporting) — no Apps Script required. The Netlify functions use a
# service account (JWT) to append rows and read data. Create a Google Cloud project,
# enable the Sheets API, create a service account, download JSON credentials, and
# share your spreadsheet with the service account email (Editor).
#
# Each wheel with “reporting” enabled gets its own tab inside this spreadsheet
# (headers + prize labels in row 2). Spins append below. Legacy single-tab mode:
# GOOGLE_SHEET_TAB=Spins!A:G (optional; only used if you do not use per-wheel tabs).
GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_EMAIL=
GOOGLE_PRIVATE_KEY=
GOOGLE_SHEET_ID=
# GOOGLE_SHEET_TAB=Spins!A:G

# Public site URL for copy-link buttons (production)
# VITE_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://rngames.netlify.app

# Admin: skip Netlify Identity (build-time). Use for static `serve dist` UI preview only.
# Rebuild admin after changing: VITE_DEV_AUTH=1 npm run build -w @rngames/admin && npm run build
# VITE_DEV_AUTH=1
